        <h2 id="questions-to-ask-before-choosing">10 questions to ask before choosing an agency</h2>
        <p>
          Use these questions when evaluating any agency, including DC technolabs. The quality of their answers tells you far more than their sales presentation.
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Can you show me results for a business similar to mine in the Ahmedabad market?</strong> Generic case studies from other cities or industries are not sufficient evidence for your specific situation.</li>
          <li><strong>Who will actually be working on my account, and what is their experience?</strong> Ask to meet the team members, not just the account director.</li>
          <li><strong>What does your onboarding process look like in the first 30 days?</strong> A good agency audits your current position before recommending anything.</li>
          <li><strong>What metrics will your reports focus on?</strong> Look for agencies that report on leads and revenue, not just traffic and impressions.</li>
          <li><strong>What is a realistic timeline for results in my category?</strong> Any agency promising Page 1 rankings in 30 days is misleading you.</li>
          <li><strong>Do I own all accounts, content, and data created during our engagement?</strong> Everything produced for your business should belong to your business.</li>
          <li><strong>What does your pricing include, and what will be billed additionally?</strong> Setup fees, creative production, and platform costs should all be disclosed upfront.</li>
          <li><strong>What are your contract terms and exit conditions?</strong> Month-to-month arrangements demonstrate confidence in results. Long lock-in periods often indicate the opposite.</li>
          <li><strong>How do you handle strategy changes if results are not coming?</strong> Look for a structured review process, not an instruction to be patient.</li>
          <li><strong>What do your current clients say about you?</strong> Ask for two or three client references you can call directly, not just written testimonials on their website.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="pricing-benchmarks-ahmedabad-2026">Pricing benchmarks for digital marketing in Ahmedabad 2026</h2>
        <p>
          Understanding typical pricing ranges helps you recognise when an offer is too good to be true or when you are being overcharged for the category of work.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>SEO retainer:</strong> Rs 15,000 to Rs 60,000 per month depending on competition level, number of pages, and the scope of content production included.</li>
          <li><strong>Google Ads management:</strong> Rs 20,000 to Rs 75,000 per month for management fee, separate from your ad spend budget.</li>
          <li><strong>Social media management:</strong> Rs 15,000 to Rs 40,000 per month for content creation and posting across 2 to 3 platforms.</li>
          <li><strong>Website design and development:</strong> Rs 25,000 to Rs 2,50,000+ depending on complexity, custom functionality, and whether e-commerce is involved.</li>
          <li><strong>Full digital marketing retainer (SEO + paid + social):</strong> Rs 60,000 to Rs 1,50,000 per month for a comprehensive engagement.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Agencies quoting significantly below these ranges are almost certainly cutting corners on quality, using automated tools rather than skilled humans, or supplementing their fees with hidden charges introduced after the contract is signed. Agencies quoting well above these ranges should be able to demonstrate proportionally better results through detailed case studies.
        </p>

        <h2 id="red-flags-when-choosing-an-agency">Red flags when evaluating Ahmedabad agencies</h2>
        <p>
          These are the warning signs we see most commonly from business owners who come to us after a disappointing experience with a previous agency.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Guaranteed Page 1 rankings within a fixed timeframe.</strong> No agency controls Google's algorithm. Any guarantee of this kind is either a misrepresentation or involves tactics that will eventually harm your site.</li>
          <li><strong>Reports that only show traffic and keyword position, never leads or revenue.</strong> Agencies that cannot demonstrate business impact through their reporting are hiding the fact that their work is not producing any.</li>
          <li><strong>Contracts that require 12 months upfront with no exit clauses.</strong> Legitimate agencies earn your business month by month. Lock-in contracts protect the agency, not the client.</li>
          <li><strong>No access to your own Google Ads account or Analytics data.</strong> You should always have admin access to every platform that holds your data and your budget.</li>
          <li><strong>Proposals that are almost identical regardless of your business type.</strong> If the proposal for your restaurant is structurally identical to what they would send a law firm, they have not understood your business at all.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="how-to-make-your-final-decision">How to make your final decision</h2>
        <p>
          After running two or three agencies through the questions above, narrow your choice based on three criteria.
        </p>
        <p>
          First, which agency understood your business and your customer most clearly during the pitch? The agency that asked the most thoughtful questions about your current customers, your best-performing products, and your competitive landscape before recommending anything is the one most likely to build a strategy that actually works.
        </p>
        <p>
          Second, which agency gave you honest rather than comfortable answers? An agency that tells you SEO takes 4 to 6 months to show meaningful results for a competitive Ahmedabad category is being truthful. An agency that promises results in 30 days is telling you what you want to hear.
        </p>
        <p>
          Third, which agency's pricing structure makes you a partner rather than a contract obligation? An agency that offers a month-to-month arrangement with clear deliverables and a structured review at 60 and 90 days is confident in their work. One that insists on a 12-month prepayment is protecting their revenue, not your results.
        </p>
        <p>
          Ahmedabad has excellent digital marketing agencies. There are also many poor ones. The questions and criteria in this guide will help you find the right fit for your business rather than signing a contract you regret within the first quarter.
        </p>

